00:10.053 --> 00:11.576
BETH ANN:
I used to play the piano.

00:11.620 --> 00:15.015
Do you still play?My husband didn't care
for my playing.

00:15.058 --> 00:17.626
Our daughter died
because of me.

00:17.669 --> 00:20.063
I'm the one who's responsible.

00:20.107 --> 00:22.631
It seems I only have
six months to live.

00:22.674 --> 00:23.936
Six months!

00:23.980 --> 00:25.634
I thought a clean break
was just better for...

00:25.677 --> 00:26.765
I'm pregnant.

00:26.809 --> 00:28.376
He got down on one knee

00:28.419 --> 00:31.074
and asked me
if I would marry him.

00:31.118 --> 00:32.684
He told me
that his marriage is ending.

00:32.728 --> 00:34.295
He said he just needs
six months.

00:34.338 --> 00:35.774
Six months.

00:35.818 --> 00:37.428
MAUREEN:
Do you know your husband's
a homosexual?

00:37.472 --> 00:38.647
He has
that new disease

00:38.690 --> 00:39.952
that all the gay men
are spreading.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.302
That's a lie.

00:41.345 --> 00:43.434
He's the third man my
husband's seen who's had it.

00:43.478 --> 00:44.740
The first two are dead.

00:44.783 --> 00:46.263
You need care.

00:46.307 --> 00:48.874
Karl, you think I'd leave you
at a time like this?

00:48.918 --> 00:50.311
TOMMY:
Cancel the trip?

00:50.354 --> 00:51.790
That's not fair.

00:51.834 --> 00:53.836
This was supposed to be
the best summer of my life.

00:53.879 --> 00:56.056
And this could be the last
summer of Karl's life,

00:56.099 --> 00:57.840
so please stop sulking.

00:58.884 --> 01:00.930
NAOMI:
What's happened to my boy?

01:00.973 --> 01:02.453
Tommy's been in a car accident.

01:02.497 --> 01:03.976
He needed some stitches.

01:04.020 --> 01:05.108
What in the world?

01:05.152 --> 01:06.588
NURSE:
Is that a tattoo?

01:06.631 --> 01:08.329
One of these days
he'll regret that.

01:08.372 --> 01:09.852
So will she.

01:09.895 --> 01:12.028
Oh. Wow.
Right?

01:12.072 --> 01:13.812
You bought me a car?
I said
I would take care of you.

01:15.205 --> 01:16.163
JADE:
You can't return the car.

01:16.206 --> 01:17.207
It's not yours.

01:17.251 --> 01:18.600
Yeah, but he's coked
out of his mind.

01:18.643 --> 01:20.210
To accept a gift from a man
in that condition

01:20.254 --> 01:21.255
is not a good look.

01:21.298 --> 01:22.995
Just give me the keys.Stop it.

01:23.039 --> 01:24.867
Go upstairs, get your stuff!

01:24.910 --> 01:28.349
I want you out of my house now!

01:28.392 --> 01:29.654
That's not gonna happen.

01:29.698 --> 01:31.178
How can I help?

01:31.221 --> 01:32.962
Tell me everything
you know about Jade.

01:33.005 --> 01:36.618
Well, for starters,
that's not her real name.

01:51.154 --> 01:54.157
♪ "L" is for the way you look

01:54.201 --> 01:57.029
